      • initialize

        public void initialize()
                throws PropertyVetoException,
                       PropertyConversionException
        Description copied from class: PropertySource
        Used for initializing the value of sources. This should be called by the Property.initialize() method only. Sources generally shouldn't be set before adding them to a property. Initialize() gives a way of setting the value of the property source when the logic for calculating the property is within the source itself. This will ensure the set value will be checked by property vetoers. If the source value is set in the constructor (of a subclass) the value will not be checked by vetoers.
        Overrides:
        initialize in class PropertySource<T>
        Throws:
        PropertyVetoException - on error
        PropertyConversionException - on error
